race.comment: KEEPMEINTHELOPE (7) was returning from a break last time out and proved too classy, scoring by 1.3 lengths over 1200m at Sunshine Coast. Open to plenty of improvement and is among the leading chances. CERTIFIED COPY (12) went forward and gave a great sight when second over 1255m at Ballina last time out. Drawn to enjoy a nice run just off the speed and is sure to be competitive. INTRUDER (6) bounced back last start and landed the prize by a head over 1350m at Ipswich. Anticipating another big run. WINCHMAN (11) is racing well and is rarely out of the money at this distance. Draws for another good showing.
